overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The
  assistant performed an initial assessment, identifying several gaps in the
  current implementation. Subsequently, the assistant began implementing the
  identified high-priority missing features. This included adding a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness interference, complete with dynamic safety
  warnings in both the interactive questionnaire and the generated PDF report.
  Additionally, the assistant implemented the detection and reporting of
  Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA), ensuring that this specific
  condition is recognized and appropriate recommendations are provided, while
  also refining the display logic for individual insomnia and sleep apnea
  diagnoses. The process involves updating data types, validation schemas, and
  UI components to reflect these new functionalities.
